    <note type="dates"><date>1822–84</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Austrian monk and botanist. Laid the mathematical foundations of the science of genetics. Conducted plant breeding experiments in the monastery garden at Brno from 1856. Published "Versuche über Pflanzenhybriden", 1866. The Mendelian laws of segregation and independent assortment derive from his work.</p></note>
